               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350921-name-527" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350921-name-527" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350921-name-527" type="surname" value="WHITE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350921-name-527" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>SARAH WHITE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of Joseph White; be keeps the Golden Fleece, in Little Knight Rider-street. On the 27th of August, the prisoner came for half a pint of porter—I served him—It came to a penny—he gave me a counterfeit shilling—I saw it was counterfeit—I charged him with it, and gave him into custody—I gave the shilling to the constable shortly afterwards.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350921-name-528" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350921-name-528" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350921-name-528" type="surname" value="MARYON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350921-name-528" type="given" value="SIMON"></interp>SIMON MARYON</persName>
                  </hi>. I took the prisoner—I searched him, and found a good shilling and two halfpence, and two duplicates—White gave me this counterfeit shilling—the prisoner was remanded the first day, and was dis<lb></lb>charged—he gave the name John Johnson.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350921-name-529" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350921-name-529" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350921-name-529" type="surname" value="ARKINSTALL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350921-name-529" type="given" value="FRANCIS"></interp>FRANCIS ARKINSTALL</persName>
                  </hi>. I am servant to George Smith; he keeps the Black Horse, in Barbican. On the 2nd of September, the prisoner came with two men and a woman—he called for a pot of porter, and gave me a counterfeit shilling—I sent for an officer—as soon as the prisoner saw our young man go out, he ran out of the door—I pursued him and gave him into custody, and gave the officer the shilling—he gave the name of John White.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350921-name-530" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350921-name-530" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350921-name-530" type="surname" value="M'DONALD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350921-name-530" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>EDWARD M'DONALD</persName>
                  </hi>. I received the prisoner, and this counterfeit shilling—I found in his left-hand pocket, a good sixpence, and some half<lb></lb>pence; and in his right-hand pocket, some sand; I suppose it is to keep the bad money rough.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
